com.camerontec.util.datamodel.expression.compiler.tree

Class ExpressionNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.datamodel.expression.compiler.tree.ExpressionNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Visitable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Array, ArrayElement, BinaryNode, Field, FieldReference, FieldReferenceLength, FieldReferenceTest, NodeWithValue, TernaryNode, UnaryNode

    public abstract class ExpressionNode
extends Object
implements Visitable
    Instances of this class are nodes in an ExpressionTree.
    Nodes can be visited as per the Visitor design pattern thanks to method accept(com.camerontec.util.datamodel.expression.compiler.tree.ExpressionTreeVisitor, com.camerontec.util.datamodel.expression.compiler.CompilationContext).
